<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Blackstone Inc. (BX)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Blackstone Inc. — using FY2025 actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026 · Data: FY2025 Financials</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">
      {currentPrice ? `vs. market price of $${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} (${marginOfSafety}%)` : 'Market price data unavailable'}
    </div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$14.45B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY2025 Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$4.5B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">$3.87</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">50.2%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">-${(Math.abs(netCash) / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model for our intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Blackstone generated <strong>$4.55 billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. This is real cash the business produces after paying for necessary capital expenditures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>15% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects Blackstone's growing AUM, especially in private credit and real estate, and recent FCF growth of 33% from FY2024 to FY2025.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3.5% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate). This captures all value from Year 6 to infinity.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>10%</strong> — our required rate of return. This aligns with the 10Y Treasury (4.18% in March 2026) plus a reasonable equity risk premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (-$10.68B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding (780M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">15%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Blackstone's FCF grew 33% year-over-year in FY2025. With massive amounts of dry powder to deploy and a booming private credit market, we model a robust 15% annual growth rate over the next 5 years.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">10%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Using the 10Y Treasury yield of 4.18% (March 2026) as a risk-free rate, plus an equity risk premium. A 10% discount rate is standard for mature alternative asset managers.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.5%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Assuming long-term nominal GDP growth plus modest pricing power, 3.5% is a steady-state assumption for an established financial powerhouse.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (FY2025)</td>
          <td>${fcf2025.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year} ({2025 + p.year})</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × 1.035)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ (10% − 3.5%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
